The paper proposes a method to optimize the activation maps of kernels in Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for specific regions of interest (ROIs) using a differentiable attention mechanism. This method is evaluated on both synthetic and natural tasks across multiple domains, indicating a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the reduction of computation in the forward pass of the network, suggesting a focus on efficiency and optimization, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), or computation and language (cs.CL).
